reviews.review: Best movie i've ever seen, it made me want to try out the Just Dance app, now free on Android and IOS. It's a shame jailbreak didn't fuck gene on the end. ????
Dab on the haters, this movie is a cinematic masterpiece that everyone needs to experience (Don't forget to download the Just Dance app now available on iOS and Android)

As I struggled to carry my medium sized popcorn on my left hand and my oversized iPhone on my right, the dread of sitting in a overcrowded theater room started to settle in.
More so because the movie I was going to see did not interest me at all. 

But that all faded once I came out with a new found hope in life. 
Joy, anger, despair, and every other emotion under the sun were felt during those profound 86 minutes.

I experienced the sorrow that Gene felt throughout the film.
I was captivated by the sheer fearlessness that Jailbreak showed. 
I fell in love with the childlike innocence that lived inside of Hi-5.

This is a true hidden gem disguised as a children's film that will surely become a cult classic in the coming years.

There are so many categories to check off on a great movie: Character development, plot, visuals, theme, the message, the time of the film, and much, much more. The Emoji Movie doesn't get a check in any of the above listed categories, and in none other that come to my mind (granted, not many can come to my mind, now that this movie has given me stage four brain cancer). Don't waste your money on this film. If you can't tell how bad the movie will be based off of this title alone, I'm sorry.

I did like the colors they used in the film. Vibrant yellow on top of vibrant yellow on top of vibrant yellow on top of vibrant yellow on top of vibrant yellow on top of some varying shades blue.
The emoji movie fun for the whole family- JacksFilms
